Privacy Policy for TapPanic

Effective Date: May 8, 2026

TapPanic (“we,” “our,” or “us”) respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how information is handled when you use the TapPanic mobile application.

Information We Collect

TapPanic is designed to collect as little personal information as possible.

The app may collect limited non-personal information automatically for functionality, analytics, performance monitoring, and advertising purposes.

Depending on features enabled in the app, the following information may be collected:

* Device type and operating system
* Anonymous gameplay statistics
* App performance and crash diagnostics
* Advertising identifiers (if advertising is enabled)
* General usage analytics

TapPanic does not intentionally collect:

* Names
* Email addresses
* Phone numbers
* Precise location data
* Payment information
* Contacts or photos

Advertising

TapPanic may display third-party advertisements through advertising partners such as:

* Google AdMob￼

Advertising providers may use device identifiers or limited usage information to provide and measure advertisements.

Users may be presented with Apple’s App Tracking Transparency permission prompt where required by iOS.

You can manage ad tracking permissions in your device settings:

* Settings → Privacy & Security → Tracking

Analytics and Diagnostics

TapPanic may use analytics or crash reporting services to improve gameplay performance, stability, and user experience.

Collected analytics information is generally anonymous and aggregated.

Data Sharing

We do not sell personal information to third parties.

Limited data may be shared with service providers solely for:

* analytics
* advertising
* crash reporting
* app functionality

Children’s Privacy

TapPanic is not directed toward children under the age of 13.

We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.

If you believe a child has provided personal information, please contact us so the information can be removed.

Data Security

We use reasonable safeguards to protect information associated with the app.

However, no method of electronic storage or transmission is completely secure.

Third-Party Services

TapPanic may rely on third-party services that maintain their own privacy policies, including:

* Apple Privacy Policy￼
* Google Privacy Policy￼

Changes to This Privacy Policy

This Privacy Policy may be updated periodically.

Changes become effective immediately upon posting the updated policy.

